One of two men charged in the killing of gay college student Matthew Shepard pleaded guilty Monday to murder, admitting he tied the bleeding young man to a wooden fence and left him for dead on the prairie.
Defense attorney Wyatt Skaggs denied that Shepard was targeted because he was gay.
